I've found another small issue on the page 114, on the chapter _Implicit parameters and conversions_ :

The code sample which in its actual form doesn't successfully compile : 

{code:language=scala}
def sum[A](xs: List[A])(m: Monoid[A]): A =
  if (xs.isEmpty) m.unit
  else m.add(xs.head, sum(m)(xs.tail)
{code}

should actually be 

{code:language=scala}
  def sum[A](xs:List[A])(m:Monoid[A]):A =
    if (xs.isEmpty) m.unit
    else m.add(xs.head, sum(xs.tail)(m))
{code}
